---
title: `$message::send()`
description: Send a HTML email.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Message::send($from, $to, $subject, $message);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
Message::send('from@mail.com', 'to@mail.com', 'Test Subject', '<p>Hello world!</p>');
~~~

~~~ .php
Message::send('from@mail.com', [
    'a@mail.com',
    'b@mail.com',
    'c@mail.com'
], 'Test Subject', '<p>Hello world!</p>');
~~~

~~~ .php
Message::send('from@mail.com', [
    'a@mail.com' => 'Person A',
    'b@mail.com' => 'Person B',
    'c@mail.com' => 'Person C'
], 'Test Subject', '<p>Hello world!</p>');
~~~